WINE, unlike fruit juice or even bour- bon, is not a fixed, re- petitive experlence— but changes its per- sonality and taste qualities as it devel- ops and matures in the bottle. Because of this, the wine-lover is prone to bea bit fickle and does not insist on drinking the same wine from day to day, no matter how good — he chooses to ad- venture among the world’s vineyards for new, interesting taste experiences.

This page includes a wide range of half bottles—all designed to assist you in em- barking on a capti- rating Odyssey of comparative tasting.

To a joyous voyage among the vineyards of the world!
